1
00:01:10,752 --> 00:01:12,431
=Those Days=

2
00:01:12,431 --> 00:01:14,800
(Adapted from iceread.com novel
"You Xi" by Qingyang Wanxi)

3
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,940
=Episode 2=

4
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:19,580
I'll drive you back.

5
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:21,020
Later, I'll take a bus to come back.

6
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:21,860
No need.

7
00:01:22,180 --> 00:01:23,660
Now you care about me.

8
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:25,980
Zhixia,

9
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:27,980
Look. Now that you're pregnant,

10
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:30,100
you should get angry less

11
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:30,980
and move around less.

12
00:01:30,980 --> 00:01:32,840
I haven't decided
whether to have the baby or not.

13
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,180
Why are you agreeing with her?

14
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,740
Of course, you want it.

15
00:01:37,740 --> 00:01:40,100
Let her make the decision.

16
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,860
Don't listen to your father.

17
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:44,020
Men know nothing

18
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:45,460
about the pain of giving birth.

19
00:01:45,660 --> 00:01:46,900
The child is already here.

20
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,100
How can she not keep it?

21
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,860
You need to respect her...

22
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:50,660
Enough.

23
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,340
I know what I know.

24
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:54,060
Yes. She can...

25
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:55,900
Just don't argue, both of you.

26
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,660
You...

27
00:01:56,660 --> 00:01:57,460
Enough.

28
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:00,940
I'm going back.

29
00:02:03,220 --> 00:02:04,660
Delete my number.

30
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:06,500
Delete it.

31
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:07,860
Be careful.

32
00:02:07,860 --> 00:02:08,940
Go.

33
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:10,900
Careful, Zhixia.

34
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,580
Dear, you are so pretty.

35
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:31,890
We'll go to the first floor for
the photoshoot when both of you are ready.

36
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:32,500
All right.

37
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:34,100
Let's go.

38
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,220
Wait.

39
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,780
You will soon become a mother.

40
00:02:42,780 --> 00:02:44,300
I must protect both of you.

41
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:54,900
When will you be home?

42
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,860
My mother is here.

43
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,340
Zhang Hao,

44
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:13,780
look.

45
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:15,020
It's full of dust.

46
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:19,020
If you don't sweep your house,
you won't dominate the world.

47
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:20,740
Wipe it off.

48
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,900
Are you judging my house
by the standards of a five-star hotel?

49
00:03:25,660 --> 00:03:26,340
What?

50
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:27,980
What are these?

51
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,580
Water bills?

52
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:31,660
More than 100 yuan for two months?

53
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:32,740
How are you using water?

54
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:33,780
How?

55
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,180
Did you open a bathhouse?

56
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:37,660
Our country's water resources

57
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,220
are very limited.

58
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,660
Come here, Mom.

59
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:41,740
Sit down.

60
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:43,140
Take a break.

61
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,620
Enough with your observation.

62
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:45,660
Isn't a home

63
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:47,180
and an enterprise the same?

64
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:48,820
If you don't have a supervision system,

65
00:03:48,820 --> 00:03:49,620
that won't do.

66
00:03:49,620 --> 00:03:50,900
It'll be ruined immediately,

67
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:52,740
with problems festering like tumors.

68
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:54,300
You're using idioms now?

69
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,180
Mom, you're here?

70
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:07,580
I heard you are pregnant

71
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:09,020
so I came here immediately

72
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:10,420
to take a look at you.

73
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:11,820
Seriously.

74
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:14,300
If you give birth to a boy,

75
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,820
you'll have a son and a daughter.

76
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:19,300
Our family's structure

77
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,900
will go through a huge change.

78
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:22,940
It'll be perfect!

79
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,140
We haven't decided
whether to have the child or not.

80
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,260
Why not?

81
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:34,820
It's expensive.

82
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:37,700
Jiao needs to learn the piano,

83
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,260
ice skating, and English.

84
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,780
They all cost money. It's expensive.

85
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,140
You have me.

86
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:43,780
I will support you.

87
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:45,260
Mom,

88
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:47,060
I thank you

89
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,740
for willing to subsidize us

90
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:52,940
but if we raise another child,

91
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:56,140
the structure of the family
will really change.

92
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:59,260
This house won't be big enough for us.

93
00:04:59,636 --> 00:05:00,916
We need a three-room unit.

94
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:05,540
I'm running a we-media account.

95
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,980
I work for myself.

96
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:10,820
I can still survive today
but I might lose my job tomorrow.

97
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:13,420
Of course, Zhang Hao's job is stable

98
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,380
but his pay is miserably low.

99
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:18,340
It's very difficult for us
to find another place to live.

100
00:05:18,340 --> 00:05:20,340
- However, I think the house...
- Let me finish.

101
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:23,580
When I had Jiao,
I was in my late twenties.

102
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,940
Now, I'm already in my late thirties.

103
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:28,660
My stamina and energy
aren't as good as they were.

104
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,340
I'm a middle-aged woman now.

105
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:31,940
I have parents and a kid
to take care of.

106
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:33,090
It's like having enemies on both sides.

107
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,380
If I raise

108
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,780
another child,

109
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:37,900
I think

110
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,860
I won't be able to handle it.

111
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:41,820
Zhixia,

112
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:44,860
I think there's always a way.

113
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,500
Look at the families of the past.

114
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,580
All of them

115
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:48,660
had more than five children.

116
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:49,660
- Yes.
- They all grew up fine.

117
00:05:49,660 --> 00:05:50,620
That's right.

118
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:52,180
That was in the past.

119
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:52,780
No.

120
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:55,460
Worry about giving birth
and not about how to raise a child.

121
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:57,860
It's the same for every generation.

122
00:05:58,180 --> 00:05:58,980
Here's what I think.

123
00:05:58,980 --> 00:06:00,660
Why is the birth rate so low?

124
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,380
Because young people

125
00:06:02,380 --> 00:06:03,700
have too many considerations

126
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:05,620
when they give birth to a child.

127
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:08,180
Zhixia,

128
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:10,060
let me take a stand right now.

129
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,660
You just need to give birth.

130
00:06:13,220 --> 00:06:15,340
The baby will
stay in your stomach for a while.

131
00:06:15,780 --> 00:06:18,300
I will feed and raise the child.

132
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:19,300
Let me

133
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:21,780
raise this child
to be the country's successor.

134
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:23,140
Mom.

135
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:24,480
- Well...
- What time is it now?

136
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:26,140
I should go back.

137
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:29,460
You are pregnant.

138
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:31,020
You need to sleep early.

139
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:31,980
Rest well.

140
00:06:32,540 --> 00:06:33,380
Rest early.

141
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,180
I'm leaving.

142
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:35,460
- Let me send you off.
- Sit down.

143
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:36,180
Don't move.

144
00:06:36,180 --> 00:06:37,700
Don't move right now.

145
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,380
I'm going back.

146
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:39,500
- Let me send you off.
- All right.

147
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,620
Mom, take care.

148
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:43,700
Slowly.

149
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,420
I'm leaving.

150
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:46,140
Take care.

151
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:47,900
Bye.

152
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:52,260
When you go out...

153
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:57,260
You speak so fast.

154
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:13,780
Let's have the baby.

155
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:16,620
My mother said she'd raise him.

156
00:07:16,860 --> 00:07:18,660
The three greatest lies of the world are

157
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:20,820
the physician's secret formula
in the martial world,

158
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,380
get-rich-quick schemes
from direct sales groups,

159
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,560
and your mother saying
she'll help you raise the child.

160
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,260
Why are you saying...

161
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,860
What's wrong with that?

162
00:07:29,460 --> 00:07:30,620
When I was pregnant with Jiao,

163
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:33,020
your mother said the same thing.

164
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:36,140
You only need to give birth.

165
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:38,250
The child will only stay
in your stomach for a while.

166
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:39,940
What next, Zhang Hao?

167
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:41,370
Before I left my confinement period,

168
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:43,060
she said her company
wants to rehire her.

169
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:45,100
It was as if
the earth needed her to spin.

170
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,980
If my mother didn't volunteer,

171
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:48,020
I couldn't even go to work

172
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:49,860
after my maternity leave.

173
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:51,140
Yes.

174
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:53,820
See? My mother is not dependable

175
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:55,780
but I am.

176
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:58,060
Have I been nurturing Jiao well

177
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,060
in every aspect
including her daily necessities?

178
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:02,380
Of course, you've contributed more.

179
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,940
I still took care of her studies, right?

180
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:06,780
You need to believe in the people.

181
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:07,620
No.

182
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:09,500
I am the people.

183
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,460
I only believe in myself.

184
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:18,860
The city

185
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,860
is still the same after all these years.

186
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,480
It's still as run down as ever.

187
00:08:22,490 --> 00:08:23,460
It has changed a little.

188
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:24,060
Mom.

189
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:25,820
This is the environment of an old city.

190
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:28,300
Look at that path along the river.

191
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,260
How beautiful it is.

192
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:30,900
If I don't drive

193
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:31,900
and ride a shared bike,

194
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,820
I'll reach the design institute
in ten minutes.

195
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:36,620
Feng Jianqi,

196
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,220
many people work their whole lives
in the old city

197
00:08:39,380 --> 00:08:42,220
just to buy a condominium with a lift

198
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:44,980
but you have given up
on your bright future

199
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:46,860
and chose a path less taken.

200
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:49,580
I don't know what you are thinking.

201
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:51,860
Your father's colleagues introduced you

202
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,380
to the daughter of a commissioner

203
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:54,540
and the niece of the chief.

204
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:56,340
All of them
were better than Shen Mingzhu.

205
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:57,780
Mom, what do you mean?

206
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:58,900
That's enough.

207
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,660
Didn't we agree
not to bring this up again?

208
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:01,660
I'm telling you.

209
00:09:01,660 --> 00:09:03,820
I am an educated person.

210
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:04,740
My culture

211
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:06,740
is built on money.

212
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:08,700
Fine. You are educated

213
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:09,580
and you are cultured.

214
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:10,220
Yes.

215
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:18,700
There are a few more dishes.

216
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:19,780
Hurry up. They'll be here soon.

217
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:20,300
It's the last one.

218
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,500
We haven't changed our clothes yet.

219
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,340
I know.

220
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:25,620
Dad!

221
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,540
You are making

222
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,660
all your secret dishes today.

223
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:29,780
Enough nonsense.

224
00:09:29,780 --> 00:09:30,940
Ask your sister

225
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:31,940
where they are now.

226
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:33,460
Mingzhu,

227
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,380
Dad is asking where Jianqi is.

228
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:36,580
They'll be here soon!

229
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,860
They have entered the old city.

230
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,320
They've entered the old city?

231
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:41,780
So many dishes.

232
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:42,780
Eat one.

233
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:44,300
You're eating already?

234
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:45,840
- They won't notice a missing prawn.
- Eat.

235
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,140
What are you doing?

236
00:09:52,140 --> 00:09:52,980
I'm blurred.

237
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:53,900
Boss, two people.

238
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:54,420
Here you go.

239
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,460
Just put it here.

240
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:58,780
Sorry.

241
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,980
There's a joyous occasion
in our family today.

242
00:10:01,780 --> 00:10:02,460
Have a cigarette.

243
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:03,860
Have a cigarette. Here.

244
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:04,460
Thank you.

245
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:07,420
We won't be opening today.

246
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:08,530
There's a joyous occasion?

247
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:09,460
All right.

248
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:10,460
- Sure.
- Sorry.

249
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,820
Hurry up.

250
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:12,420
Come again.

251
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:13,060
Sure.

252
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:14,580
Hang up the sign saying we are closed.

253
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:14,940
Hurry up.

254
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,820
Mom, help me clean up.

255
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:16,380
I...

256
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:17,980
This kid.

257
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:19,220
Shen, hurry up!

258
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:20,500
Get changed!

259
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,330
Your face is so oily.

260
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:21,780
Throw this.

261
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:22,860
Give it to me.

262
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:24,140
Quickly! Go upstairs!

263
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,420
Go and get changed. Hurry.

264
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:26,380
Go on.

265
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:28,380
(Western Ginseng, Expiry Date)

266
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:30,460
The Western Ginseng is going to expire.

267
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,180
There's still a month to go.

268
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,860
Tell them to eat it quickly.

269
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:35,700
It's very nourishing.

270
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:41,180
Mom,

271
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:42,580
this is not right.

272
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,660
What's not right about it?

273
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:46,180
The Western Ginseng is very expensive,

274
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:46,900
I'm telling you.

275
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,060
I'm sure they won't
spend money to buy it.

276
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,340
Jianqi, let me tell you.

277
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:51,620
Western Ginseng must be kept dry.

278
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:53,340
It can still be eaten
as long as it's not expired.

279
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,060
It's fine.

280
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:54,740
That's right.

281
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:57,340
Dad. This is not about
whether it can still be eaten or not

282
00:10:57,350 --> 00:10:59,260
but whether we are
showing them respect or not.

283
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,960
Feng Jianqi, what are you talking about?

284
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,180
How are we not respecting them?

285
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:04,660
Both of us

